                <h2>The Post-Procedure Sensation: The Sunburn</h2>

                <p>While the actual mechanical stamping is massively tolerable, many patients aggressively ask: <strong>is microneedling painful</strong> immediately <em>after</em> the clinic appointment concludes?</p>

                <p>Exactly three to four hours after you leave DenceSpot Clinic Gurgaon, the thick, heavy Lidocaine completely metabolizes and aggressively wears off. Your brain suddenly receives the urgent, delayed signals that your face was severely micro-injured. It is at this precise moment that the famous "Microneedling Sunburn" sets in heavily.</p>

                <p>Your face will look intensely crimson red and radiate an incredibly high geometric volume of heat. It will feel exquisitely tight, dry, and massively pulse with a dull, throbbing raw sensitivity. It feels exactly identical to falling asleep violently bare-faced on a tropical beach for four hours without sunscreen.</p>

                <p>However, this is strictly a superficial, highly annoying discomfort, not excruciating sharp pain. The profound burning sensation peaks rapidly roughly 12 hours post-procedure and then precipitously drops off dramatically by the 24-hour mark. If we heavily supplement your treatment using <a href="does-prp-work-for-hair-loss.php">your own PRP platelets</a> (creating a Vampire Facial), the rich organic growth factors massively slash this burning downtime in half.</p>

